cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection in images using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach that directly generates the saliency map without the need for pixel-level annotations or object proposals, which involves machine learning (cs.AI), and the use of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the approach, which involves evaluation metrics and comparisons with existing methods, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
